#1 Download data: click on links in pdfs, will take you to NCBI, scroll down then click on the ID under Run, 
   will take you SRA page, click data access, copy link 2 and download run with wget - do for all four
   
#2 Python code to make input - fasta file Script: 02_generate.py
      output fasta file and log file
   build index with kallisto using fasta file
   kallisto index -i hcmv_index.idx HCMV_reads.fasta

#3 Quantify the TPM of each CDS using kallisto (do for each SRR)
   kallisto quant -i hcmv_index.idx -o quant_results_SRR5660030 -b 30 -t 4 SRR5660030.1_1.fastq SRR5660030.1_2.fastq
   Generates input for sleuth (R) - find differentially expressed genes between the two timepoints (2pi and 6dpi)
   Sleuth with R script 03

#4 Create an index with Bowtie2:
   bowtie2-build HCMV_reads.fasta HCMV
      outputs 6 files
   Map to the index (all four SRRs): ##need to filter out reads that don't map!!
   bowtie2 --quiet -x --no-unal HCMV -1 SRR_seq_data/SRR5660030.1_1.fastq -2 SRR_seq_data/SRR5660030.1_2.fastq -SHCMV_SRR30map.sam
      outputs 4 .sam files
   Add to log file:
   printf "Donor 1 (2dpi) had " >> miniProject.log
   wc -l SRR5660044.1_1.fastq *2 will get total number of initial reads
   " read pairs before Bowtie2 filtering and " >> miniProject.log
   grep --count ^SRR5660030 HCMV_SRR30map.sam #lines that start with SRR#
   " read pairs after.\n" >> miniProject.log

#5 Convert .sam files to fastq files for SPAdes input (for all 4 SRRs):
   samtools fastq HCMV_SRR30map.sam > spades_input_HCMV_SRR30.fastq
   Run SPAdes and write command used to log file:
   
   printf "spades command" >> miniProject.log

